00:47:41.936 --> 00:47:43.560
Could you clearly
define the difference

00:47:43.560 --> 00:47:45.265
between polyamory and polygamy?

00:47:45.265 --> 00:47:46.640
DEDEKER WINSTON:
Yes, yeah, 100%.

00:47:46.640 --> 00:47:47.820
EMILY MATLACK: Absolutely.

00:47:47.820 --> 00:47:49.080
DEDEKER WINSTON: And
it just goes-- really,

00:47:49.080 --> 00:47:49.870
it's quite simple.

00:47:49.870 --> 00:47:52.170
It goes down to just
the roots of the word.

00:47:52.170 --> 00:47:55.740
So poly meaning many,
amory meaning love.

00:47:55.740 --> 00:47:59.130
Polygamy-- so gamy
refers to spouse.

00:47:59.130 --> 00:48:01.470
So specifically, it
means many spouses.

00:48:01.470 --> 00:48:03.480
It's not gender specific.

00:48:03.480 --> 00:48:05.790
We have a term polygyny,
which is having

00:48:05.790 --> 00:48:07.200
multiple female partners.

00:48:07.200 --> 00:48:10.020
Or polyandry, which is
multiple male partners.

00:48:10.020 --> 00:48:14.460
But culturally, when people
use the word polygamy,

00:48:14.460 --> 00:48:16.780
the image that comes to
mind is bearded men named

00:48:16.780 --> 00:48:18.412
Ezekiel with child brides.

00:48:18.412 --> 00:48:20.370
That's what we think of
when we think polygamy.

00:48:20.370 --> 00:48:23.910
And so even though polygamy
just means multiple spouses,

00:48:23.910 --> 00:48:25.620
we usually try to
discourage people

00:48:25.620 --> 00:48:28.080
from using polyamory and
polygamy interchangeably,

00:48:28.080 --> 00:48:31.080
just because of the fact that
polygamy carries this really

00:48:31.080 --> 00:48:32.770
charged image along with it.

00:48:32.770 --> 00:48:34.020
JASE LINDGREN: A very sexist--

00:48:34.020 --> 00:48:36.210
DEDEKER WINSTON: And a very
sexist, unhealthy image.

00:48:36.210 --> 00:48:37.668
EMILY MATLACK:
Polyamory, you don't

00:48:37.668 --> 00:48:40.470
have to be married, whereas
the assumption is, in what,

00:48:40.470 --> 00:48:42.480
polygamy, that
people are married,

00:48:42.480 --> 00:48:43.749
but there are multiple wives.

00:48:43.749 --> 00:48:44.790
JASE LINDGREN: Thank you.

